"{\"agreements\":[{\"point\":\"Webhook processing must be made asynchronous or non-blocking to prevent timeouts under load\",\"supportingAgents\":[\"senior-engineer\",\"performance-engineer\",\"security-engineer\"],\"reasoning\":\"All three agree that synchronous webhook handling creates scalability and reliability risks. The senior engineer now endorses async processing, the performance engineer insists on it, and the security engineer’s structural validation requires robust event handling.\",\"evidenceChain\":[\"cmqnt9zi9000d5ep3tsyx4dg7\",\"cmqntadvi00215ep3gina2asj\",\"cmqntaqjf003k5ep3k94ap92g\"]},{\"point\":\"Plan selection must occur after authentication to prevent pricing enumeration\",\"supportingAgents\":[\"product-engineer\",\"security-engineer\"],\"reasoning\":\"The product engineer revised their proposal to require authentication before showing plan options, directly addressing the security engineer’s critical concern about unauthenticated access to pricing data.\",\"evidenceChain\":[\"cmqntadvh00205ep31lk5uypq\",\"cmqntaqjk003n5ep3qj6ucifo\"]},{\"point\":\"User-facing feedback (e.g., toasts) must be validated/sanitized to prevent XSS and information leaks\",\"supportingAgents\":[\"product-engineer\",\"security-engineer\"],\"reasoning\":\"Both agree that action feedback is essential for UX but must be implemented securely with server-side validation and content sanitization.\",\"evidenceChain\":[\"cmqntadvh00205ep31lk5uypq\",\"cmqntaqjk003n5ep3qj6ucifo\"]},{\"point\":\"The current billing logic is overly coupled and needs architectural refactoring\",\"supportingAgents\":[\"senior-engineer\",\"performance-engineer\"],\"reasoning\":\"Even the performance engineer acknowledges the 'God object' problem in utils/supabase/admin.ts and tight coupling in the webhook handler, though they differ on the solution’s performance impact.\",\"evidenceChain\":[\"cmqnt9zi4000b5ep3n93twgk7\",\"cmqntadvi00215ep3gina2asj\"]}],\"disagreements\":[{\"point\":\"How to optimize account page data fetching: batched JOIN vs. parallel queries\",\"positions\":[{\"agentId\":\"performance-engineer\",\"stance\":\"Prefer parallel execution with Promise.all to avoid RLS complexity\",\"reasoning\":\"Parallel calls maintain existing security boundaries without requiring complex RLS policy validation for joins.\"},{\"agentId\":\"senior-engineer\",\"stance\":\"Open to batching if RLS policies are verified\",\"reasoning\":\"Batching may offer better performance if RLS supports safe cross-table joins; otherwise, parallel is acceptable.\"}],\"evidenceChain\":[\"cmqnt9zi9000d5ep3tsyx4dg7\",\"cmqntadvg001z5ep3pod8ug82\",\"cmqntaqji003m5ep360lgoifl\"]},{\"point\":\"Level of authorization required for profile updates\",\"positions\":[{\"agentId\":\"security-engineer\",\"stance\":\"Require re-authentication or at least rate limiting + audit trails\",\"reasoning\":\"Session hijacking is a real risk; sensitive operations need stronger protection than just being behind auth.\"},{\"agentId\":\"product-engineer\",\"stance\":\"Avoid re-authentication due to UX friction; basic auth may suffice\",\"reasoning\":\"Re-authentication harms conversion; most users don’t frequently change emails, so risk is low relative to cost.\"}],\"evidenceChain\":[\"cmqnt9zi6000c5ep3u8akrh9r\",\"cmqntadvi00225ep3jac8ql28\",\"cmqntaqjh003l5ep3sk4infdv\"]}],\"recommendedDecisions\":[{\"title\":\"Implement asynchronous webhook processing with immediate acknowledgment\",\"description\":\"Return 200 OK immediately from /api/webhooks/route and process events in the background using database-persisted jobs (not external queues) to avoid timeouts while minimizing new infrastructure.\",\"confidence\":0.9},{\"title\":\"Introduce a performance-aware Billing Service Layer\",\"description\":\"Refactor billing logic into services/billing/ with connection pooling, prepared statements, and optional caching—but only after validating performance impact in staging.\",\"confidence\":0.85},{\"title\":\"Require authentication before plan selection\",\"description\":\"Show plan options only after user signs up and is authenticated, preventing unauthenticated pricing enumeration while preserving core UX benefit.\",\"confidence\":0.9},{\"title\":\"Add route-level authorization middleware for protected paths\",\"description\":\"Enforce that /account and payment routes are accessible only to authenticated users, with future extensibility for roles. Do not implement full RBAC yet.\",\"confidence\":0.8}],\"identifiedRisks\":[{\"description\":\"Background webhook processing may lose events during edge function cold starts\",\"severity\":\"high\",\"raisedBy\":[\"performance-engineer\"]},{\"description\":\"Post-authentication plan selection may reduce signup conversion\",\"severity\":\"medium\",\"raisedBy\":[\"product-engineer\"]},{\"description\":\"Batched account page queries may violate RLS and expose user data\",\"severity\":\"high\",\"raisedBy\":[\"senior-engineer\"]},{\"description\":\"Stripe webhook lacks structural validation, enabling business logic manipulation\",\"severity\":\"high\",\"raisedBy\":[\"security-engineer\"]}],\"openQuestions\":[\"Is Supabase RLS configured to safely support JOINs across user, user_details, and subscriptions tables?\",\"Can Stripe guarantee event ordering (product.created before price.created) to eliminate foreign key retries?\",\"What percentage of users perform sensitive profile operations, justifying re-authentication UX cost?\",\"Are there existing patterns for safe background task execution in this codebase?\"],\"overallConfidence\":0.82,\"artifactOperations\":[{\"operation\":\"reject\",\"artifactId\":\"decision-Add plan selection step to signup flow\",\"title\":\"Add plan selection step to signup flow\",\"sourceEventId\":\"cmqnt9zi9000e5ep39bq64f7m\"},{\"operation\":\"create\",\"type\":\"decision\",\"title\":\"Require authentication before plan selection\",\"content\":\"Move plan selection to post-authentication flow rather than during signup. Show plan options after user creates account but before redirecting to Stripe. This maintains the product benefit while respecting security boundaries.\",\"sourceEventId\":\"cmqntaqjk003n5ep3qj6ucifo\"},{\"operation\":\"update\",\"artifactId\":\"decision-Implement Asynchronous Webhook Processing\",\"title\":\"Implement Asynchronous Webhook Processing\",\"content\":\"Return 200 OK immediately from webhook handler and process events in background using database-persisted jobs (not external queues). This prevents timeouts while avoiding operational complexity of queue systems.\",\"sourceEventId\":\"cmqntaqji003m5ep360lgoifl\"},{\"operation\":\"accept\",\"artifactId\":\"recommendation-Add webhook event schema validation with Zod\",\"title\":\"Add webhook event schema validation with Zod\",\"sourceEventId\":\"cmqntaqjh003l5ep3sk4infdv\"},{\"operation\":\"accept\",\"artifactId\":\"decision-Optimize account page queries with parallel execution instead of batching\",\"title\":\"Optimize account page queries with parallel execution instead of batching\",\"sourceEventId\":\"cmqntaqji003m5ep360lgoifl\"}]}"